… Calls attackers misguided Nigerians The Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, was, on Friday, attacked in Spain by some persons he described as “misguided Nigerians.” Amaechi disclosed on his Twitter handle, @ChibuikeAmaechi, that
he was attacked at an event on climate change held in Madrid, Spain. He said Spanish policemen managed to stop his attackers before they could hurt him, but did not disclose their identities. “Some minutes ago, I was attacked by a few misguided Nigerians while on national assignment at a climate change event in Madrid, Spain. They were quickly repelled by the Spanish police before they could do any harm. I am fine. I was not hurt. Thanks for your support & prayers,” the Minister tweeted. 